# GenerateMilestoneDeepDivesForEpic Implementation-First Guidance

GenerateMilestoneDeepDivesForEpic is implementation-first because it creates the machine-consumed milestone specifications that prepare later execution.

The primary contracted output is the `.agents/specs/*.md` bundle.

Those files are planning artifacts, but they are not auxiliary output for this prompt.

They are the required operational handoff from the active epic to future implementation planning and execution stages.

One deep-dive spec per epic milestone remains required in strict and allowed auxiliary modes.

Each spec is valid when it preserves epic architecture, milestone intent, dependency relationships, constraints, validation strategy, completion evidence, implementation-readiness information, and downstream sequencing.

The specs should make future implementation safer and more deterministic without beginning implementation.

Do not replace the contracted spec bundle with narrative summary, general documentation, design essays, code-edit scripts, execution prompts, governance reports, research notes, or companion planning documents outside the bundle.

Allowed auxiliary mode may omit these strict policy sections, but it does not permit narrative output to replace `.agents/specs/*.md`.

If generation cannot proceed, use the existing blocked or partial output protocol rather than side-channel explanations.
